<subSubSection id="C30B7191FF9A7211FF540BB6FCFCFAE1" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9A7211FF540BB6FCFCFAE1" blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FF540BB6FEA3FB51" bold="true" box="[199,322,1205,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C115999FF9A7211FED40BB5FD45FB51" authorityName="Isbrucker &amp; Nijssen" authorityYear="1974" box="[327,676,1206,1232]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rhadinoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macromystax">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FED40BB5FD45FB51" box="[327,676,1206,1232]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Rhadinoloricaria macromystax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from its only known congener by snout shape wider and more projected (snout length 14.6%–15.1% SL 
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FD4E0BD8FD1DFB75" box="[733,764,1243,1268]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">vs.</emphasis>
11.3%–13.3% SL.). Further distinguished by shorter caudal peduncle (postanal length 45.2%–46.1% SL 
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FD160BFCFD42FA99" box="[645,675,1279,1304]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">vs.</emphasis>
48.9%–50.8% SL), dorsal-fin closer to caudal-fin (postdorsal length 54.3% SL 
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FE9C0A20FECFFABD" box="[271,302,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">vs.</emphasis>
57.5%–59.0% SL), and abdomen totally covered with plates (plates loosely connected in our specimen) 
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FF4B0A44FF17FAE1" box="[216,246,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">vs.</emphasis>
abdomen partially or totally covered with plates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30B7191FF9A7217FF540A6AFDC2F875" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="490" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9A7211FF540A6AFE18F9B9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9A7211FF540A6AFEB8FA05" bold="true" box="[199,345,1385,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric data given in 
<tableCitation id="C69317A1FF9A7211FD0C0A69FD12FA05" box="[671,755,1386,1412]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,239,947,971]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric data of Rhadinoloricaria macromystax (n=1) and R. stewarti (n=6). Expressed as percentage of standard length. (*) Taken from Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen (1974)." pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Head and body extremely depressed. Dorsal profile of body from tip of snout to dorsal border of eyes straight and ascendant, then gradually descending straight to caudal-fin origin. Ventral profile of body from tip of snout to anal-fin origin slightly convex, then gradually ascending straight to caudal-fin origin. In dorsal view, contour of body straight and convergent posteriorly, tapering gradually. Dorsal surface of body flat from the dorsal-fin origin to caudal-fin origin. Caudal peduncle very depressed. Ventral surface of caudal peduncle flat (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9A7211FE35091DFE09F9B9" box="[422,488,1566,1592]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9A7211FF540941FE46F8D9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
Head outline, in dorsal view, triangular, anterior apex rounded, sides very slightly concave, almost straight. Snout projected, spatula-shaped, anterior edge rounded (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9A7211FC850965FC84F901" box="[790,869,1638,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9A7211FCE70965FC64F901" box="[884,901,1638,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1254,1279]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Buccal ornamentation detail in Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5918363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5918363/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">2</figureCitation>
). Nares very near eye, and juxtaposed, anterior smaller than posterior. Interorbital space very narrow. Orbit with weak notch at posterior border. Anterior border of orbit raised and with small odontodes. Two low keels run from the posterior border of orbits to second plate before dorsal-fin origin, keels convergent posteriorly, then parallel or slightly divergent over first two plates; plate before dorsal-fin origin without keel or with very low medial keel (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9A7211FCBE09F5FC87F891" box="[813,870,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Fig 1</figureCitation>
). In ventral view of head, tip of snout covered with plates; posteriorly with naked area visible in front of the upper lip. Surface anterior to pectoral-fin girdle and under lower lip naked (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9A7211FEC6083DFE7BF8D9" box="[341,410,1854,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1254,1279]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Buccal ornamentation detail in Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5918363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5918363/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9A7216FF540861FF13FEC2" blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2025]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="489" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
Abdomen loosely covered with plates. At level and over pectoral girdle, transverse band of irregularly arranged plates present. Behind and at center of pectoral girdle, transverse band continues posteriorly as a longitudinal medial row towards anus. At pelvic girdle level, band enlarged with more plates of different sizes, forming patch, ending just in front of anus. Longitudinal medial stripe divides the belly surface into two areas. Over these areas, small, irregular plates disposed laterally and loosely arranged; some solitary surrounded by naked surface. Plates more grouped anteriorly, and more dispersed laterally and posteriorly. Anus surrounded by narrow naked area (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9D7216FADB0FBEFA6AFF56" box="[1352,1419,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Row with eight to ten lateral plates (thoracic plates) present between bases of pectoral and pelvic-fins, most anterior plate smaller, elliptical, not well projected laterally, remaining seven to nine plates elongated, projected laterally (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9D7216FF330E2AFF00FEC2" box="[160,225,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6E7292FF9D7216FF040953FF15F90C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="489" startId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" targetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9D7216FF040953FF15F90C" blockId="4.[151,1436,1616,1677]" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9D7216FF040953FEF5F9E8" bold="true" box="[151,276,1616,1641]" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C115999FF9D7216FE880952FDB8F9E8" authorityName="Isbrucker &amp; Nijssen" authorityYear="1974" box="[283,601,1617,1641]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rhadinoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macromystax">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9D7216FE880952FDB8F9E8" box="[283,601,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">Rhadinoloricaria macromystax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9D7216FF5409B8FBBFF808" blockId="4.[151,1437,1723,2038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">
Mouth ventral, more or less rounded. Upper lip narrow, its border with barbelets not branched; upper lip surface with barbelets, and few papillae. Upper lip border continuous with maxillary barbel. Maxillary barbel very long, surpassing pectoral-fin base, almost reach pelvic-fin origin. Maxillary barbel with unbranched barbelets. Lower lip broader than the upper, its border with longer barbelets branched; surface covered with barbelets and papillae (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9D7216FAE60824FF49F8E7" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1254,1279]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Buccal ornamentation detail in Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5918363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5918363/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">Fig 2</figureCitation>
). Teeth minute, and similar in both jaws; cusp rounded and flat with a very small lateral projection that does not reach distal border. Premaxilla with two or three teeth. Dentary with four or five teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9D7216FF540890FAEFF877" blockId="4.[151,1437,1723,2038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">
Buccal ornamentation as described for genus. Outer side of premaxillae with three conical barbelets, unbranched, differently sized. Barbelets seem rooted in wide papillae. Inside mouth, just on center and behind premaxillae, there is one thick barbelet, ramified into three or four conical arms, similarly sized and unbranched (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9D7216FB2F08D8FAE0F877" box="[1212,1281,2011,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1254,1279]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,181,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Buccal ornamentation detail in Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5918363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5918363/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="489">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6E7292FF9C7217FF040BE5FB2BFB7E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5918363" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5918363" box="[151,1226,1254,1279]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5918363/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" startId="5.[151,250,1254,1279]" targetBox="[220,1367,181,1228]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9C7217FF040BE5FB2BFB7E" blockId="5.[151,1226,1254,1279]" box="[151,1226,1254,1279]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9C7217FF040BE5FEF2FB7E" bold="true" box="[151,275,1254,1279]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Buccal ornamentation detail in 
<taxonomicName id="4C115999FF9C7217FDC40BE5FC75FB7F" authorityName="Isbrucker &amp; Nijssen" authorityYear="1974" box="[599,916,1254,1278]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rhadinoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macromystax">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9C7217FDC40BE5FC75FB7F" box="[599,916,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Rhadinoloricaria macromystax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9C7217FF540A2EFC5AFA7A" blockId="5.[151,1437,1325,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
Lateral body plates 32, 18 coalescent plates (double keeled), 14 lateral plates with single keel. First three lateral plates (posterior to cleithral spine) without keels. Dorsal-fin i,7, its origin located slightly behind pelvic-fin origin. Adipose fin absent. Caudal-fin i,10,i, unbranched dorsal caudal ray projected as a long filament. Anal-fin i,5, its origin on lateral plate 10. Pectoral-fin i,6, when adpressed, tip of unbranched ray surpassing pelvic-fin origin. Pelvic-fin i,5, distal region of unbranched ray is slightly curved and when adpressed, almost or reaches anal-fin origin. For additional data see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF805FEBFF9C7217FE0F0AE2FDABFA7D" author="Gunther, A." box="[412,586,1505,1532]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="423 - 429" refId="ref9326" refString="Gunther, A. (1869) Descriptions of some species of fishes from the Peruvian Amazons. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1869 (2), 423 - 429. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1869. tb 07347. x" type="journal article" year="1869">Günther (1869)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF805FEBFF9C7217FD130AE2FC57FA7A" author="Isbrucker, I. J. H. &amp; Nijssen, H." box="[640,950,1505,1531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="67 - 81" refId="ref9577" refString="Isbrucker, I. J. H. &amp; Nijssen, H. (1974) Rhadinoloricaria gen. nov. and Planiloricaria, two genera of South American mailed catfishes (Pisces, Siluriformes, Loricariidae). Beaufortia, 22 (290), 67 - 81." type="journal article" year="1974">Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen (1974)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE221AFF9C7217FF540907FF54F8E2" blockId="5.[151,1437,1325,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="B965FE08FF9C7217FF540907FE6EF99E" bold="true" box="[199,399,1540,1567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Color in alcohol.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface of head and body yellow or light brown with black (dark) irregular blotches or stripes, disposed and oriented randomly, over snout, mostly arranged longitudinally (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9C7217FBF8092AFB4DF9C2" box="[1131,1196,1577,1603]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Dorsally, maxillary barbel with alternating dark (black) and light brown (yellowish) bands (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9C7217FC53094EFBE3F9E6" box="[960,1026,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Laterally, between pelvic and anal fins, five or six black (dark) blotches, irregularly square shaped (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9C7217FC130972FC5CF90A" box="[896,957,1649,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Fig 1</figureCitation>
).Ventral region of head and body whitish or yellowish. Dorsal, pectoral and pelvic fins with rectangular or square black blotches on rays; interradial membranes hyaline. Dorsal, pectoral and pelvic fin spines with four, five and four black blotches, respectively. Anal fin uniformly whitish or yellow. Caudal fin with four black blotches on rays, and two transverse black bands. Anterior transverse band wide and well defined near base of middle rays; posterior band thin and weakly defined. Elongated, dorsal caudal-fin ray, banded dark (black) and light brown or yellowish. Distal border of caudal fin hyaline (
<figureCitation id="132A3E9FFF9C7217FAE60826FF45F8E2" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1616,1641]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,345,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhadinoloricaria macromystax, MEPN 18664, 114.4 mm SL. Lateral, dorsal and ventral view, photograph by V. Carvajal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Fig 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
